\frame{\titlepage}

\begin{frame}{Anime Statistics and Analysis Platform (ASAP)}
\phantomsection\label{anime-statistics-and-analysis-platform-asap}
\emph{Authors: Qiran Hu (qiranhu2), Zoey Yao (wanjing4)}

From Subculture To Mainstream: Examining Anime's Transformation From
Microculture Into Global Mainstream Through User Engagements

The anime culture has become a global phenomenon that significantly
influences popular culture and shapes the entertainment industry
worldwide with skyrocketed revenues and unprecedented international
growth in recent years.

This research examines the key factors of anime's global market
expansion through ``anime content creations and distributions'' and
analyzes their implications for stakeholders and investors as well as
regular anime fans.

\begin{itemize}
\tightlist
\item
  \textbf{Improving Anime Fan Experience}\\
\item
  \textbf{Current Obstacles With Anime Market}\\
\item
  \textbf{Improving Industry Stakeholders Experience}
\end{itemize}

------------------------------------------------------------------------\newpage
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}{Data Preprocessing}
\phantomsection\label{data-preprocessing}
Handling Missing Values

\begin{itemize}
\item
  NA rows were removed
\item
  A lot of data
\end{itemize}

Predictive Model Data Preprocessing

\begin{itemize}
\item
  \textbf{Producer:} split individual, criteria
\item
  \textbf{Studios:} criteria
\item
  \textbf{Type:} ANOVA, Tukey Test, criteria
\item
  \textbf{Genres:} encodes top 10 with one-hot encoding
\item
  \textbf{Ratings:} ANOVA, Tukey Test, criteria
\end{itemize}

\includegraphics[width=0.5\textwidth,height=\textheight]{../AdditionalResources/1.png}

------------------------------------------------------------------------\newpage
\end{frame}

\begin{frame}[fragile]{Predictive Model \textbf{Training, Validation,
and Testing Set}}
\phantomsection\label{predictive-model-training-validation-and-testing-set}
\begin{verbatim}
→ 10‐fold Cross Validation 
\end{verbatim}

Linear Regression Model

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Linearly predicts the score by giving different weights to
  predictors\\
\item
  Shows a sigmoid shape when plotting
\end{itemize}

Random Forest

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Multiple decision trees contribute to the model
\item
  Almost perfect alignment
\end{itemize}

