\end{frame}

\begin{frame}[fragile]{Future Plans And Set Ups}
\phantomsection\label{future-plans-and-set-ups}
As the global anime market continues its expansion, our proposed
platform offers various benefits to both anime fans and stakeholders.
However, as entertainment technology and consumer behavior rapidly
evolve, we hope to extend our research to improve the user experience
and address specific limitations in our current platform.

\begin{itemize}
\item
  Large Language Model Integration And Machine Learning Algorithms\\
\item
  Multimedia Performance Evaluation\\
\item
  User-Contributed Database\\
\item
  Global Expansion And Creator Support\\
\item
  Live Event Integration And Virtual Conventions
\end{itemize}

Set Ups

Running Our Application Locally

Clone the repository located at\\
\url{https://github.com/illinois-stat447/sp25-prj-qiranhu2-wanjing4}.\\
With the \texttt{app.R} file still open in RStudio, click the
\textbf{Run App} button (the green ▶️ icon at the top of the source
editor).

Using Online Version

If you prefer not to install anything, you can access the Anime
Statistics and Analysis Platform directly in your web browser:\\
\url{https://qiranhu.shinyapps.io/AnimeStatisticsandAnalysisPlatform/}

------------------------------------------------------------------------\\
\end{frame}

